{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Building a Sioux Falls Network"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import geopandas as gpd\n",
    "import networkx as nx\n",
    "import osmnx as ox\n",
    "import larch"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from larch.util import cache_requests"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sf = ox.gdf_from_place('Sioux Falls')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We'll add a small buffer around the actual city limits, and download all\n",
    "the streets inside the buffer from Open Street Map."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 64,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "bounds = gpd.GeoDataFrame(geometry=sf.buffer(0.02)).bounds"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Getting an Open Street Map network\n",
    "\n",
    "Now let's get the OpenStreetMap network within the study area."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 65,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "streets = ox.graph_from_bbox(bounds.maxy[0], bounds.miny[0], bounds.maxx[0], bounds.minx[0], simplify=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "How much network did we get?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 66,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(53856, 111430)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 66,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "len(streets.nodes), len(streets.edges)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 67,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 521.987x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = ox.plot_graph(streets)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### View the set of all highway types"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 45,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'cycleway': 6086,\n",
       " 'footway': 7736,\n",
       " 'motorway': 1354,\n",
       " 'motorway_link': 2465,\n",
       " 'path': 3000,\n",
       " 'planned': 46,\n",
       " 'primary': 1467,\n",
       " 'primary_link': 50,\n",
       " 'residential': 43811,\n",
       " 'road': 100,\n",
       " 'secondary': 4834,\n",
       " 'secondary_link': 109,\n",
       " 'service': 26194,\n",
       " 'steps': 10,\n",
       " 'tertiary': 7247,\n",
       " 'tertiary_link': 141,\n",
       " 'track': 1368,\n",
       " 'trunk': 505,\n",
       " 'trunk_link': 158,\n",
       " 'unclassified': 4749}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 45,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "highway_types = []\n",
    "for i in streets.edges.values():\n",
    "    highway_types.append(str(i['highway']))\n",
    "unique_highway_types, count_highway_types = np.unique(highway_types, return_counts=True)\n",
    "link_type_counts = {}\n",
    "for u, c in zip(unique_highway_types, count_highway_types):\n",
    "    link_type_counts[u] = c\n",
    "link_type_counts"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Remove Minor Link Types\n",
    "\n",
    "There are a lot of pedestrial and minor links in this network.  Let's abandon all these low level links."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "major_types = {\n",
    "    'motorway', 'motorway_link', \n",
    "    'primary', 'primary_link',\n",
    "    'secondary', 'secondary_link', \n",
    "    'tertiary', 'tertiary_link',\n",
    "}\n",
    "streets.remove_edges_from( [ \n",
    "    k for (k,v) in streets.edges.items() \n",
    "    if v.get('highway') not in major_types\n",
    "] )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 48,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(53856, 17667)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 48,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# How much network do we have left? \n",
    "len(streets.nodes), len(streets.edges)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 49,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 521.918x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = ox.plot_graph(streets)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "There are a lot of leftover unconnected nodes -- when we dropped \n",
    "residential streets, we didn't drop those nodes.  Let's do that now."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 50,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 521.918x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "streets.remove_nodes_from(\n",
    "    list(nx.isolates(streets)) # list-ify to gather nodes first then remove them\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig, ax = ox.plot_graph(streets)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Better!  How much network now?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 51,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(11616, 17667)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 51,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "len(streets.nodes), len(streets.edges)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Check for unconnected network parts\n",
    "\n",
    "To check for network connectivity, we'll find shortest paths from one node to all other nodes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 68,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "a_node = list(streets.nodes)[0] # Grab a node ID randomly\n",
    "\n",
    "# Nodes that can be reached from a_node\n",
    "connected_nodes_out = set(nx.shortest_path(streets, source=a_node, weight='length').keys())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Nodes that can reach a_node\n",
    "connected_nodes_in = set(nx.shortest_path(streets, target=a_node, weight='length').keys())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Nodes that are full connected \n",
    "connected_nodes = connected_nodes_out & connected_nodes_in\n",
    "\n",
    "# The rest\n",
    "unconnected_nodes = [node for node in streets.nodes() if node not in connected_nodes]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's view a map of the unconnected nodes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 69,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 521.987x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "nc = ['w' if node in connected_nodes else 'r' for node in streets.nodes()]\n",
    "fig, ax = ox.plot_graph(streets, node_color=nc)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Looks like the unconnected nodes are for the most part on divided highways that leave the study area.\n",
    "This makes sense, and in a complete demand model these would get external stations\n",
    "at the ends.  But let's just drop them for this example."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 61,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "streets.remove_nodes_from(unconnected_nodes)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 62,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(11106, 11106)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 62,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "len(connected_nodes), len(streets)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 63,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 522.207x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = ox.plot_graph(streets)"
   ]
  },
